<link href='https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Caveat Brush' rel='stylesheet'>

<%= render 'shared/header' %>
<div class='container'>
  <div class='content'>
    <%= render 'shared/sidebar' %>
    <div class='picture'>

      <div class="polaroid">
        <%= image_tag('garlic_butter_steak_and_potatoes.png', :alt => 'Garlic Butter Steak and Potatoes Skillet') %>
        <div class="polaroid_container">
          <p class='content_description'>
            Garlic Butter Steak and Potatoes Skillet
          </p>
          <p>
            <%= link_to "Reddit User: Divider1 - Reddit",
            "https://www.reddit.com/r/recipes/comments/8f1xrm/garlic_butter_steak_and_potatoes_skillet/",
            :target => "_blank" %>
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class='description'>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a>
              <h2>Description:</h2>
              <p>
                You can never go wrong with a steak unless you go well done...
              </p>
              <p>
                Prep: 15 mins
                Cook: 10 mins
              </p>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class='ingredients'>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <a>
              <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
              <ul>
                <li> STEAK AND POTATOES </li>
                <li> 1 1/2 lb (650g) flank steak, sliced against the grain </li>
                <li> 1 1/2 lb (650g) baby yellow potatoes, quartered </li>
                <li> 1 tablespoon olive oil </li>
                <li> 3 tablespoons butter, divided </li>
                <li> 5 garlic cloves, minced </li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon fresh thyme, chopped </li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon fresh rosemary, chopped </li>
                <li> 1 teaspoon fresh oregano, chopped </li>
                <li> Salt and fresh cracked pepper </li>
                <li> Crushed red chili pepper flakes, optional </li>
                <li> MARINADE </li>
                <li> 1/3 cup soy sauce </li>
                <li> 1 tablespoon olive oil </li>
                <li> 1 tablespoon hot sauce (we used Sriracha) </li>
                <li> Fresh cracked pepper </li>
              </ul>
            </a>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class='method'>
      <div class='method_text'>
        <p>Method</p>
      </div>
      <div class='method_steps'>
        <ol>
          <p>
            In a large bowl, combine the steak strips with soy sauce, olive oil,
            pepper, and hot sauce. Set aside to marinate while you cook potatoes.
          </p>
          <p>
            In a large skillet over medium-high heat, mix 1 tablespoon olive oil
            and 1 tablespoon butter. When butter is melted, add potatoes. Cook
            for about 4 minutes, stir and cook an additional 4-5 minutes until
            potatoes are golden and fork tender. Transfer to a plate and set aside.
          </p>
          <p>
            Keep the same skillet over medium heat and add remaining 2
            tablespoons butter, garlic, red chili pepper flakes, and fresh herbs.
            Lay the steak strips in one layer in the skillet, keeping the drained
            marinade for later. Cook on each side for 1 minute each, until nicely
            browned â€“ adjust timing depending on how you like your steak.
          </p>
          <p>
            Right before the steak is done, you can stir in the reserved
            marinade if you like, and cook for one minute. Add the potatoes back
            to the pan and heat through. Adjust seasoning with salt and pepper
            if necessary.
          </p>
          <p>
            Remove from heat and serve immediately, garnished with more crushed
            chili pepper, fresh herbs, and a sprinkle of parmesan cheese over
            the potatoes if you like. Enjoy!
          </p>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <%= render 'shared/footer' %>
</div>
